Speaker B: So, actually, when I was looking at it, I was. I didn't realize that it would go through to the booking, so I haven't actually decided yet, but I didn't look like there was any way to cancel what I'd already done, so.
Speaker A: Actually, the booking hasn't been processed for any of them. I see. I think that you have shown interest. I just wanted to confirm, like, which will be your top choice for the accommodation so that I can get to, you know, reserve a group.
Speaker B: So, like, I. I haven't quite decided, so would it be possible to, for the moment, just. Just cancel them?
Speaker A: Would you. Would you like to have any suggestions for the same.
Speaker B: Pardon?
Speaker A: Would you like to have any suggestions from my end, like, which properties should. Sorry, could you just rep. Yes. What I'm saying here is, would you like to have some suggestions? Like what. Which property should you choose from my end? I'll do one thing here, Melinda. I'll connect you one more step. Will that be okay for you? I suppose that the network line is not very good, even.
